# This working tree is SHARED between Linux and Windows (dual-boot, one drive).
# Linux executes these files directly from this checkout, so a CRLF rewrite by
# the Windows side (core.autocrlf=true) would break every #!/bin/bash shebang,
# systemd unit, and cron-invoked script. Pin them to LF regardless of local
# autocrlf settings; .bat is the one family cmd.exe wants CRLF.
*.sh      text eol=lf
*.py      text eol=lf
*.service text eol=lf
*.desktop text eol=lf
Makefile  text eol=lf
# -text (not "text eol=crlf"): the .bat blobs are committed WITH CRLF already;
# a text attribute would demand LF-normalized blobs and flag them all modified.
*.bat     -text
